<?php $__env->startSection('postContent'); ?><p><strong>Purpose:</strong></p>
<p>To develop the skills, knowledge and confidence associated with creating and performing work. Drama is offered as a subject at all levels in the school. Students can work towards national qualifications such as achievement standards.</p>
<p><strong>Content:</strong></p>
<p>In Year 9, we focus on extending personal skills such as communication, self-confidence, listening and co-operation. Students work in groups and are introduced to a number of theatre forms such as mime and improvisation. Alongside the practical work, students maintain a drama portfolio in which they evaluate their work and identify future targets.</p>
<p><strong>Assessment:</strong></p>
<p>Process-rehearsal work and written portfolio. Practical - performance based.</p><?php $__env->stopSection(); ?>
